ona Stoyanova","SS","https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3914-9569",{"_":184,"xml:id":185,"ref":186},"Alessia Coccato","Coccato","https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6641-2820",{"_":188,"when":189,"who":190},"Marta Fogagnolo revised the text encoding, added dimensions, translations and commentary","2022-12-22","#martaf",{"n":103,"url":104,"height":105,"width":106,"desc":107,"surfaceType":108},[193],{"atLeast":194,"atMost":195},30,32,[197,198],"Korhonen, 2004, IMusCatania","Libertini, 1930, Il Museo Biscari",[200,201],"2EUC82DH","SKUU2R8X",[203,204,205,21,26,206,207,208,209,210,208,211,212,125],"isic003296","fragment of an epitaph",{"_":5},"fine-grained, homogeneous, white marble, likely lunense, docimian, göktepe, pentelic. digital microscopy: homeoblastic fabric (identification based on pxrf, digital microscopy)","catina","catania","sicilia","sicily","museo civico di catania","ancient greek",[],{"title":215,"body":216,"divs":217,"editions":244,"images":254,"handnote":260},"ISic003296. Fragment of an epitaph","\u003Cdiv id=\"editions\">\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Marta Fogagnolo, Alex Antoniou\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"δώρα\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"δώρα\">[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>δ]ώρα\u003C/span>\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"ἡ\">ἡ\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"σεμνοτάτη\">σεμ-\u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>[νοτάτη?\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"μάμμη\">μ?]άμμη\u003C/span>  \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Marta Fogagnolo, Alex Antoniou\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"δώρα\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"δώρα\">[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>.]ΩΡΑ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"ἡ\">Η\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"σεμνοτάτη\">ΣΕΜ\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>[......\u003C/span>\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"μάμμη\">.]ΑΜΜΗ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003296_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic003296_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003296.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic003296-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text based on photograph\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Apparently there is no text before l. 1\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 1\">line.1: \u003Cspan>Korhonen: [---δ]ώρα (possibly Ἰσιδώρα or Θεοδώρα)\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"lines 1-2\">lines.1-2: \u003Cspan>Korhonen: σεμ|[νοτάτη]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 2\">line.2: \u003Cspan>Korhonen: [μ]άμμη (or ἀμμή)\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5187-5163\">Marta Fogagnolo\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>… -dora, the noblest … mother.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>Italian translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5187-5163\">Marta Fogagnolo\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>… -dora, la nobilissima … madre.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>The inscription is very fragmentary. Korhonen recognised at ll. 1-2 a traditional epithet characterising women in Christian epitaphs, \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">σεμνοτάτη\u003C/span> (other epithets are \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ἀγνοτάτη\u003C/span>, \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">πιστοτάτη\u003C/span>, or \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">εὐλαβεστάτη\u003C/span>, on which see F. Grossi Gondi, \"Trattato di epigrafia cristiana latina e greca del mondo romano occidentale\" (Roma, 1920), 171-177; Korhonen 2004: 111). The name of the deceased was supposed to be either \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Ἰσιδώρα\u003C/span> or \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Θεοδώρα\u003C/span>, names that recur in Christian Sicilian funerary inscriptions (the former appears in an inscription from Catania of the Byzantine period, IMusCatania 191 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic003289\" target=\"_blank\">ISic003289\u003C/a>, the latter in an inscription from Syracuse of the V-VI cent. CE, SEG 4.2 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic003178\" target=\"_blank\">ISic003178\u003C/a>). The term \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">μάμμη\u003C/span> (or \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ἀμμή\u003C/span>) is affective and recurs in another inscription from Catania of IV-V cent. CE, Libertini (1931), 44 no.7 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001629\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001629\u003C/a>.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Libertini 1930 317 no.4 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001871\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001871\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Korhonen 2004 204 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Korhonen 2004 p. 111 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"handnote\">\u003Cp>Letters with apices, A with sloping bar, lunate Ε and Σ, cursive Ω. Μ and Η in ligature at l. 2.\u003C/p> Lines 1-2  30-32  Interlineation line 1 to 2  not recorded  \u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. \u003C/div>",[218,221,224,227,230,232,235,238,241],{"id":219,"html":220},"editions","\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Marta Fogagnolo, Alex Antoniou\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"δώρα\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"δώρα\">[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>δ]ώρα\u003C/span>\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"ἡ\">ἡ\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"σεμνοτάτη\">σεμ-\u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>[νοτάτη?\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"μάμμη\">μ?]άμμη\u003C/span>  \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Marta Fogagnolo, Alex Antoniou\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"δώρα\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"δώρα\">[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>.]ΩΡΑ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"ἡ\">Η\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"σεμνοτάτη\">ΣΕΜ\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>[......\u003C/span>\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"μάμμη\">.]ΑΜΜΗ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>",{"id":222,"html":223},"facsimile-images","\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003296_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic003296_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003296.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic003296-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>",{"id":225,"html":226},"apparatus","\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text based on photograph\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Apparently there is no text before l. 1\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 1\">line.1: \u003Cspan>Korhonen: [---δ]ώρα (possibly Ἰσιδώρα or Θεοδώρα)\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"lines 1-2\">lines.1-2: \u003Cspan>Korhonen: σεμ|[νοτάτη]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 2\">line.2: \u003Cspan>Korhonen: [μ]άμμη (or ἀμμή)\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>",{"id":228,"html":229},"translation","\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5187-5163\">Marta Fogagnolo\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>… -dora, the noblest … mother.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":228,"html":231},"\u003Ch2>Italian translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5187-5163\">Marta Fogagnolo\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>… -dora, la nobilissima … madre.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":233,"html":234},"commentary","\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>The inscription is very fragmentary. Korhonen recognised at ll. 1-2 a traditional epithet characterising women in Christian epitaphs, \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">σεμνοτάτη\u003C/span> (other epithets are \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ἀγνοτάτη\u003C/span>, \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">πιστοτάτη\u003C/span>, or \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">εὐλαβεστάτη\u003C/span>, on which see F. Grossi Gondi, \"Trattato di epigrafia cristiana latina e greca del mondo romano occidentale\" (Roma, 1920), 171-177; Korhonen 2004: 111). The name of the deceased was supposed to be either \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Ἰσιδώρα\u003C/span> or \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Θεοδώρα\u003C/span>, names that recur in Christian Sicilian funerary inscriptions (the former appears in an inscription from Catania of the Byzantine period, IMusCatania 191 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic003289\" target=\"_blank\">ISic003289\u003C/a>, the latter in an inscription from Syracuse of the V-VI cent. CE, SEG 4.2 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic003178\" target=\"_blank\">ISic003178\u003C/a>). The term \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">μάμμη\u003C/span> (or \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ἀμμή\u003C/span>) is affective and recurs in another inscription from Catania of IV-V cent. CE, Libertini (1931), 44 no.7 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001629\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001629\u003C/a>.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":236,"html":237},"bibliography","\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Libertini 1930 317 no.4 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001871\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001871\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Korhonen 2004 204 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Korhonen 2004 p. 111 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  ",{"id":239,"html":240},"handnote","\u003Cp>Letters with apices, A with sloping bar, lunate Ε and Σ, cursive Ω. Μ and Η in ligature at l. 2.\u003C/p> Lines 1-2  30-32  Interlineation line 1 to 2  not recorded  ",{"id":242,"html":243},"license"," Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. ",[245,247,250,251],{"html":246},"Text encoding: Marta Fogagnolo, Alex Antoniou",{"id":248,"lang":125,"html":249},"edition-interpretive","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"δώρα\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"δώρα\">[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>δ]ώρα\u003C/span>\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"ἡ\">ἡ\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"σεμνοτάτη\">σεμ-\u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>[νοτάτη?\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"μάμμη\">μ?]άμμη\u003C/span>  \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"html":246},{"id":252,"lang":125,"html":253},"edition-diplomatic","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"δώρα\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"δώρα\">[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>.]ΩΡΑ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"ἡ\">Η\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"σεμνοτάτη\">ΣΕΜ\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>[......\u003C/span>\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"μάμμη\">.]ΑΜΜΗ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",[255,257],{"image":104,"thumb":256,"title":107},"ISic003296_tiled-thumb.tif",{"image":258,"thumb":259,"title":107},"ISic003296.jpg","ISic003296-thumb.jpg",[261],{"html":61},"\u003C?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>\n\u003C?xml-model href=\"https://epidoc.stoa.org/schema/latest/tei-epidoc.rng\" type=\"application/xml\" schematypens=\"http://relaxng.org/ns/structure/1.0\"?>\n\u003C?xml-model href=\"../schematron/ircyr-checking.sch\" schematypens=\"http://purl.oclc.org/dsdl/schematron\"?>\n\u003CTEI xmlns=\"http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0\" xmlns:xi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude\" xml:lang=\"en\">\n    \u003CteiHeader>\n        \u003CfileDesc>\n            \u003CtitleStmt>\n                \u003Ctitle>Fragment of an epitaph\u003C/title>\n                \u003Ceditor ref=\"#JP\">Jonatha